HEADWORD: Disbud
<hw>Dis*bud"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Bud</er>,
<pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Hort.)</fld> <def>To deprive of buds or
shoots, as for training, or economizing the vital strength of a
tree.</def>⟦br⟧
